parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning backup camera can increase the risk of accidents, particularly when reversing, as the driver may not have a clear view of the surroundings.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a blurry image
or an upside-down image; the camera fails to function while reversing; the camera image goes in and out or flickers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling and hesitation of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially in heavy traffic or when carrying passengers.
symptoms: The engine stalls or hesitates when accelerating; the engine stalls in traffic or when backing out of a driveway; the engine goes into a protection mode without warning lights; the vehicle consumes excessive oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause difficulty or inability to steer the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control, especially during turns or when navigating tight spaces.
symptoms: loud squealing sound when turning the steering wheel
front end of the vehicle bouncing

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear backup camera can cause a safety hazard by obstructing the driver's view while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear backup camera display is upside down
the rear backup camera display is flashing in and out
the rear backup camera display is black
the rear backup camera display is malfunctioning intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire tread belt can cause sudden tire blowouts, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Bubbles or blisters on the tire sidewall
vibration or shaking of the vehicle.
